description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amazing and unique opportunity in one of the country’s biggest NHS Trusts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an amazing and unique opportunity in the Communications Team at Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust – one of the biggest NHS Trust’s in the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a vibrant, confident, creative and passionate colleague to join our team for this newly created role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need experience of planning and delivery of events, on both a small and larger scale, negotiating with suppliers, along with experience of sourcing sponsorship funding to ensure that the awards process is sustainable. You will be friendly, approachable, and good at building relationships quickly at all levels of the organisation and with partners externally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be to take a lead role in day to day management of the organisation’s value based awards programme – the Team NUH awards –alongside other internal awards programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be expected to seek out opportunities for staff and services at Nottingham University Hospitals to be entered into local and national awards in recognition of their work and/ innovations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be able to establish positive working relationships and manage a busy workload, responding to conflicting priorities as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think you have what it takes to make this role a success and deliver results then you might just be the person we’re looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tiffany Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Director of Communications and Engagement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tiffany.Jones@nuh.nhs.uk / 07812 269880&lt;/p&gt;
